<statement>
<image width="33%" pi:generated="problems/images/mom-1057071-1.png"/><p>
Suppose a = 4 and c = 8. Calculate:</p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle{b}\approx</m> <input type="text" style="width:5.8ch" name="qn1000" id="qn1000" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 1 of 3" class="text"/></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle{A}\approx</m> <input type="text" style="width:5.8ch" name="qn1001" id="qn1001" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 2 of 3" class="text"/> degrees</p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle{B}\approx</m> <input type="text" style="width:5.8ch" name="qn1002" id="qn1002" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 3 of 3" class="text"/> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>6.9</li><li>30.0</li><li>60.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}^{{2}}={4}^{{2}}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{64}={16}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{64}-{16}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{48}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle\sqrt{{{48}}}={b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{6.9282032302755}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{6.9}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arcsin{{\left(\frac{{4}}{{8}}\right)}}}\approx{30}\approx{30}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arccos{{\left(\frac{{4}}{{8}}\right)}}}\approx{60}\approx{60}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>